## How to Add a New Page

{% if router == "app-router" %}
### App Router (file-based routing)

1. Create a folder under `src/app/` matching the URL path.
2. Add a `page.tsx` file - this is the page component.
3. Add a `loading.tsx` for the Suspense fallback.
4. Add a `error.tsx` for the error boundary.
5. If the page needs data, fetch it directly in the `page.tsx` (it is a Server Component by default).

**Example: adding `/products` page**

```
src/app/(dashboard)/products/
├── page.tsx          # async Server Component - fetch data here
├── loading.tsx       # skeleton shown while page data loads
└── error.tsx         # error shown if page throws
```

```tsx
// src/app/(dashboard)/products/page.tsx
import { Suspense } from "react";
import { getProducts } from "@/services/products";
import { ProductTable } from "@/components/features/products/ProductTable";
import { ProductTableSkeleton } from "@/components/features/products/ProductTable.skeleton";

export const metadata = { title: "Products | {{ display_name }}" };

export default async function ProductsPage() {
  // Server Component: direct async call, no useEffect, no useState
  const products = await getProducts();

  return (
    <div className="space-y-6 p-6">
      <h1 className="text-2xl font-semibold">Products</h1>
      <Suspense fallback={<ProductTableSkeleton />}>
        <ProductTable products={products} />
      </Suspense>
    </div>
  );
}
```

{% else %}
### Pages Router (file-based routing)

1. Create a `.tsx` file under `src/pages/` matching the URL.
2. Export a default React component.
3. Add `getServerSideProps` or `getStaticProps` for data fetching.

**Example: adding `/products` page**

```tsx
// src/pages/products/index.tsx
import type { GetServerSideProps, NextPage } from "next";
import type { Product } from "@/types/product";
import { ProductTable } from "@/components/features/products/ProductTable";
import { getProducts } from "@/services/products";

interface Props {
  products: Product[];
}

const ProductsPage: NextPage<Props> = ({ products }) => {
  return (
    <div className="space-y-6 p-6">
      <h1 className="text-2xl font-semibold">Products</h1>
      <ProductTable products={products} />
    </div>
  );
};

export const getServerSideProps: GetServerSideProps<Props> = async () => {
  const products = await getProducts();
  return { props: { products } };
};

export default ProductsPage;
```

{% endif %}

