## Styling Conventions

{% if styling == "tailwind" %}
- Use Tailwind utility classes directly in JSX
- For variant-based components, use `cva` from `class-variance-authority`
- Merge conditional classes with `cn()` from `src/lib/utils.ts` (wraps `clsx` + `tailwind-merge`)
- Use semantic colour tokens (`text-foreground`, `bg-card`, `border-border`) NOT raw values (`text-gray-900`)
- Never use `@apply` in component files
- Never use inline `style` props for visual styling

```tsx
// Good
<div className={cn("rounded-lg border bg-card p-4", isActive && "border-primary")}>

// Avoid
{{ '<div style={{ borderRadius: "8px", background: "white" }}>' }}
```

{% elif styling == "css-modules" %}
- Every component has a colocated `.module.css` file
- Class names use camelCase: `styles.cardHeader`, not `styles['card-header']`
- Global styles (tokens, resets) are in `src/styles/` only - never write global selectors in module files
- Do not use inline `style` props for visual styling

```tsx
import styles from "./ProductCard.module.css";
<div className={styles.card}>
```

{% elif styling == "styled-components" %}
- All styles use `styled` components or the `css` helper from styled-components
- Theme values come from `useTheme()` - never hardcode hex values
- Do not mix styled-components with inline `style` props
- Avoid deeply nested selectors - create a new styled component instead

{% elif styling == "scss" %}
- Component styles use colocated `.module.scss` files
- Global tokens are in `src/styles/abstracts/` as SCSS variables and custom properties
- Use SCSS variables for design tokens, CSS custom properties for runtime theming
- Avoid nesting more than 2 levels deep in SCSS

{% endif %}

{% if design_style == "minimal-clean" %}
### Design Guidance: Minimal-Clean

- Generous whitespace: prefer `p-6`, `gap-6`, `space-y-6`
- Restrained colour palette: `foreground`, `muted-foreground`, `primary` only
- Subtle borders and shadows: `border`, `shadow-sm` - not `shadow-xl`
- Typography hierarchy: `text-2xl font-semibold` (h1), `text-xl font-medium` (h2), `text-base` (body)
- No decorative gradients or illustrations on functional pages

{% elif design_style == "corporate-professional" %}
### Design Guidance: Corporate-Professional

- Structured, grid-based layouts with clear visual hierarchy
- Blue/grey primary colour scheme (configure in `tailwind.config.ts`)
- Data density: prefer tables and compact lists over cards
- Formal language in empty states and error messages
- Consistent action placement: primary actions always top-right

{% elif design_style == "playful-modern" %}
### Design Guidance: Playful-Modern

- Rounded corners: `rounded-xl` or `rounded-2xl` for cards
- Vibrant accent colours with gradients for hero elements
- Micro-interactions: use CSS transitions for hover states, focus rings
- Friendly, conversational empty state messages
- Icons alongside labels for most actions

{% endif %}

